{
  "stem": "3022.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we gave them all the food that we brought with us, everything that we had.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And at one point, the woman got up and they said, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] it's time to light Shabbos candle-- [SOBBING] it was time to light Shabbos candles.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We had no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I mean, for us, Shabbos didn't mean anything anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We didn't even know that it was a Friday night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And yet these women, with kerchiefs on their head, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] lit the candles.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the six of us, the men slowly broke out into the Shabbos song of welcome, Shalom aleichum, and we linked arms.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And somehow, we felt that we were victorious, that we defied the designs of the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we survived, not only in flesh [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] but in spirit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Strangely as it may seem, there was hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Because we looked at Jewish women, and we knew there were going be Jewish home, there were going to be Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we were not vanquished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It took a long time afterwards before we saw another Jewish woman.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And shortly after this, I joined my friend Oscar and went to work for the American Army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "As I told you, it was the 35th Tank Battalion.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "The captain on our unit was a wonderful man, Captain Kingsley.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He was a teacher from Buffalo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And when we became so taken with stories about American life that the GIs used to tell us, we made the decision, both Oscar and I, that we want to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "When he heard that, he said, well, if you want to go the States, why don't you get an education.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There's nothing that will help you as much as an education.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know the extent of my education.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
